  "description": [
    "Page Six THS PJMiy WORKER Published by the DAILY WORKER PUBLISHING CO 1640 N Hals ted St Chicago 111 Phone Lincoln 7680 SUBSCRIPTION RATES By mail 600 per year 3606 months 2003 months By mail in Chicago only SSOO per year 4506 months 260 months Address all mail and make out checks to THE DAILY WORKER 1640 N Halsted Street Chicago Illinois J LOUIS ENGDAHL Editors WILLIAM F DUNNE i MORITZ J LOEB Business Manager Entered as secondclass mail Sept 21 1923 at the Office at Chicago 111 under the act of March 3 Made in America The injunction is a distinctly American weapon used by the bosses in their struggle with the workers The injunction enables the employer to rob the workingman of every advantage that the strike can net him as a means of selfdefense The injunction makes every possible effect of every strike impossible It is a declaration of martial iaw by the government in behalf of the bosses against the workers The injunction begins with the assumption that the workingman has committed a crime It assumes that the workingman is guilty until he can prove to a hostile judge who is district attorney judge and jury"
